Nadine Strossen :
" People will often ask me , “ Was n’t it hard for you when the ACLU defended the rights of the Nazis to march in Skokie ? ” No ! For me , it ’s never about the Nazis , it ’s about freedom of speech . It ’s about the principle . So I tend to see things in a rather abstract level . For every bad piece of mail I receive , I get marriage proposals , love letters , letters of praise ! " All photos :
David Shankbone
